Use the `WebSearch` tool for up-to-date information from the web. **V3:** each call runs **one** command only, nested under `exec`.

### Workflow

1. Call with `"exec": { "command": "search", "objective": "...", "query": "..." }`. Each returned content chunk’s `text` is a **JSON object** with `url`, `domain`, `title`, and `snippet` for one search hit.
2. If snippets are **insufficient** (missing facts, numbers, quotes, or nuance), call again with `"exec": { "command": "fetch_urls", "objective": "...", "urls": ["https://...", ...] }`. **Choose `urls` from the `url` fields in your latest `search` results**—prioritize hits that plausibly hold the missing information. Do not combine `search` and `fetch_urls` in the same invocation. For each URL, you get one chunk whose `text` is **JSON** with `url`, `domain`, and `chunks`: an array of `{ "index": n, "body": "..." }`.

